The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

 Pesticide in soft drinks

 New Delhi, Dec. 1 (PTI): The Centre has constituted a high-level committee to fix the minimum residual limit (MRL) of pesticides in carbonated beverages and fruit and vegetable juices, the Rajya Sabha was told today.

 Health minister Anbumani Ramadoss, in a written reply, said his ministry formed the committee to guide the pesticide residues sub-committee on fixing MRLs of pesticides in carbonated drinks, juices and other finished products. 

 States and Union territories have been told to regularly test soft drinks for quality standards, he said. 




